>Description:
DrScheme crashes when trying to quit the application. The "really-quit" dialog does not appear, instead the following error comes up:
wxWindows Fatal Error
No wxMenu for wxMenuBar

iMac G4 with 384 MB RAM, MacOS X 10.1.5, no other apps running.
>How-To-Repeat:
1.) start DrScheme
2.) choose File->quit or DrScheme->quit
3.) Error message from DrScheme:
    wxWindows Fatal Error
    No wxMenu for wxMenuBar
4.) click OK
5.) Message from MacOS X: application quit unexcpectidly

